<paragraph id="8BE3860FFFEBFFE9FCF4F876073EFEA8" blockId="7.[810,1420,1933,2091]" lastBlockId="8.[168,778,160,563]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="487" pageId="7" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFEBFFE6FCF4F87606E7F84D" bold="true" box="[810,971,1933,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="486">Identification.</emphasis>
Plants dull green. Ventral merophyte of 2 cells wide. Leaves imbricate, ovate-oblong, apex rounded or acute to acuminate, margin entire to slightly crenate; median cells hexagonal, trigones large, cuticle strongly papillose. Lobules ovate, 1/5 lobe length, apical tooth short, straight to falcate. Underleaves distant to contiguous, bifid, ovate, 2‒3 × stem width, base cordate, apex narrowly triangular to acuminate ending of 2‒5 cells in a row, margin entire, plane. Perianth obovate, 5-keeled, keels with teeth, cilia and lacinia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE3860FFFE4FFE9FF10FEB1073DFE01" blockId="8.[168,778,160,563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicName id="4C5CFD8CFFE4FFE9FF10FEB104EDFE89" box="[206,449,330,353]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="487" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="controversa">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE4FFE9FF10FEB104EDFE89" box="[206,449,330,353]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="487">Lejeunea controversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly characterized by having the underleaves (2‒3 × stem width) with the apex narrowly triangular to acuminate (ending of 2‒5 cells in a row), a strongly papillose cuticle, and a 5-keeled perianth with teeth, cilia, and lacinia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
